The doc says:

> Until TYPO3 4.5: list of page_ids
> Since TYPO3 4.6: list of page_ids /stdWrap

This is not correct. When you look at the code in @ContentObjectRenderer::getWhere()@ you can see that uidInList is compared to the uid field:

<pre>
$listArr = GeneralUtility::intExplode(',', str_replace('this', $GLOBALS['TSFE']->contentPid, $conf['uidInList']));
if (count($listArr) == 1) {
	$query .= ' AND ' . $table . '.uid=' . (int)$listArr[0];
} else {
	$query .= ' AND ' . $table . '.uid IN (' . implode(',', $GLOBALS['TYPO3_DB']->cleanIntArray($listArr)) . ')';
}
</pre>

@(One sentence moved to #56917.)@

#53910 introduces a API so you can register your own FileCollection types. Is is also possible to override core FileCollection types.

How to use:

# Create your own FileCollection class that extends \TYPO3\CMS\Core\Resource\Collection\AbstractFileCollection 
<pre>
namespace MyVendor\MyExtionsion\Collection;

class MyFileCollection extends \TYPO3\CMS\Core\Resource\Collection\AbstractFileCollection {

	/**
	 * Populates the content-entries of the collection
	 *
	 * @return void
	 */
	public function loadContents() {
		// load your files and
		// add them to to collection
		// with $this->add($file);
	}
}
</pre>
# Register type in ext_localconf.php
<pre>
  /** @var $registry TYPO3\CMS\Core\Resource\Collection\FileCollectionRegistry */
  $registry = \TYPO3\CMS\Core\Utility\GeneralUtility::makeInstance('TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\Collection\\FileCollectionRegistry');
  $registry->registerFileCollectionClass('MyVendor\\MyExtionsion\\Collection\\MyFileCollection', 'my_type');
</pre>
# Add type to TCA in Configuration/TCA/Overrides/sys_file_collection.php
<pre>
  /** @var $registry TYPO3\CMS\Core\Resource\Collection\FileCollectionRegistry */
  $registry = \TYPO3\CMS\Core\Utility\GeneralUtility::makeInstance('TYPO3\\CMS\\Core\\Resource\\Collection\\FileCollectionRegistry');
  $registry->addTypeToTCA('my_type', 'My filecollection', 'needed,fields,comma,separated');
  return $GLOBALS['TCA']['sys_file_collection'];
</pre>

#53130 adds new property "direction" in sorting to order fileObjects in reverse order.

if (is_array($conf['sorting.']) && isset($conf['sorting.']['direction']) && strtolower($conf['sorting.']['direction']) === 'desc') {
    $fileObjects = array_reverse($fileObjects);
}

Document keywords/possible values "asc" and "desc" with default "asc".
